      <div class="docs-eyebrow">Admin Panel</div>
      <h1 class="docs-title">Episode Template Editor</h1>
      <p class="docs-lead">
        The Episode Template Editor defines the fields that appear on game topics (episodes) —
        the structured header shown at the top of an in-character thread. Use it to capture
        metadata like a cover image, timeline period, or episode summary that applies to the
        thread as a whole rather than to any individual post.
      </p>

      <div class="docs-screenshot">
        <img src="/assets/screenshots/admin-game-header-template.png" alt="Episode Template Editor screenshot" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">How it works</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        The interface is identical to the
        <a href="/docs/admin-character-template/" class="docs-link">Character Template Editor</a>.
        Each row defines one field; the order of rows controls the order fields appear in the
        episode header. When a member creates a new game topic, they fill in these fields before
        the thread begins.
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        Renaming a <strong>Machine Field Name</strong> after episodes have been created will
        disconnect it from stored data. Treat machine names as permanent once episodes exist.
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Field properties</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        All field properties are the same as in the
        <a href="/docs/admin-character-template/" class="docs-link">Character Template Editor</a>.
        Refer to that page for a full description of Machine Field Name, Human Field Name,
        Field Type, Content Field Type, Order, and Width / Height.
      </p>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Example template</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        A typical episode header might use the following fields:
      </p>

      <table class="docs-table" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Machine Name</th>
            <th>Human Name</th>
            <th>Field Type</th>
            <th>Content Type</th>
            <th>Order</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>image</code></td><td>Cover Image</td><td>string</td><td>cropped_image</td><td>1</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>episode_type</code></td><td>Timeline</td><td>string</td><td>short_text</td><td>2</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>description</code></td><td>Episode Summary</td><td>text</td><td>long_text</td><td>3</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">Managing fields</h2>

      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Add Field</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Appends a new blank field row. Fill in all properties before saving.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Remove</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Removes the field from the editor. The change is not permanent until you click <strong>Save</strong>.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field-row">
          <div class="field-meta">
            <div class="field-name">Save</div>
          </div>
          <div class="field-desc">
            Saves the entire episode template in one go.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
